00:17:26.670 --> 00:17:28.200
OK, so that's the idea.

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:31.500
So that's-- what this is
supposed to motivate is why we

00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:34.530
like to think about systems in
terms of frequency response.

00:17:34.530 --> 00:17:38.760
It's a natural way to think
of certain kinds of systems.

00:17:38.760 --> 00:17:42.870
Just like the time response,
the impulse response,

00:17:42.870 --> 00:17:45.360
the time domain
thinking convolution,

00:17:45.360 --> 00:17:48.450
was a convenient way to think
about some kinds of systems,

00:17:48.450 --> 00:17:50.040
the optical system.

00:17:50.040 --> 00:17:51.780
Frequency response is
a good way to think

00:17:51.780 --> 00:17:53.580
about some kinds of systems.

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:54.687
Here's one.

00:17:54.687 --> 00:17:56.520
The reason it's a good
way to think about it

00:17:56.520 --> 00:18:00.060
is that this particular
system had a big response

00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:02.640
at a certain frequency.

00:18:02.640 --> 00:18:05.390
OK, now for something that
has nothing to do with 003.

00:18:05.390 --> 00:18:07.520
Why is the CD there?

00:18:12.400 --> 00:18:13.376
Yes.

00:18:13.376 --> 00:18:14.850
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:18:14.850 --> 00:18:16.641
DENNIS FREEMAN: It keep
it-- so it somewhat

00:18:16.641 --> 00:18:17.895
