00:46:03.800 --> 00:46:05.390
The shape of the
curve's upside down,

00:46:05.390 --> 00:46:08.840
because the pole's
in the bottom.

00:46:08.840 --> 00:46:13.310
Longer arrows now make
smaller eigenvalues.

00:46:13.310 --> 00:46:16.480
So now as you go to
higher frequencies,

00:46:16.480 --> 00:46:18.990
the idea is that a
single pole gives you

00:46:18.990 --> 00:46:21.670
a frequency response,
whose magnitude

00:46:21.670 --> 00:46:26.890
decays as you deviate from 0.

00:46:26.890 --> 00:46:29.080
And you get
increasing phase lag.

00:46:29.080 --> 00:46:32.290
You get increasing phase lag,
because this angle increases

00:46:32.290 --> 00:46:36.869
with omega, but
it's in the bottom.

00:46:36.869 --> 00:46:38.910
Increases in the bottom,
that means it decreases.

00:46:38.910 --> 00:46:41.100
That's why the angle
goes down, in this case.

00:46:41.100 --> 00:46:44.670
And if you have a pole
and a 0, the answer

00:46:44.670 --> 00:46:48.450
is easily derived from
the previous two answers.

00:46:48.450 --> 00:46:52.710
You think about two vectors, one
connecting the 0 to the point

00:46:52.710 --> 00:46:56.990
at the frequency of interest,
the other connecting the pole.

00:46:56.990 --> 00:46:59.490
And the magnitude is the product
to the lengths of those two

00:46:59.490 --> 00:47:02.400
vectors, and the angle is the
sum of the angles of those two

00:47:02.400 --> 00:47:04.660
vectors.

00:47:04.660 --> 00:47:07.440
So you can see that the
0 is slightly shorter

00:47:07.440 --> 00:47:12.270
at low frequencies, and becomes
asymptotically the same length.

00:47:12.270 --> 00:47:13.860
That means that at
high frequencies

00:47:13.860 --> 00:47:16.860
the magnitude goes to
1, except, of course,

00:47:16.860 --> 00:47:20.730
I've got a constant
here, so it goes to 3.

00:47:20.730 --> 00:47:23.520
And at low frequencies,
this length

00:47:23.520 --> 00:47:25.800
is shorter than that one,
so it's slightly smaller.

00:47:25.800 --> 00:47:29.010
The magnitude smaller
lower frequencies.

00:47:29.010 --> 00:47:32.250
Similarly for the angles, the
angles both start out at 0,

00:47:32.250 --> 00:47:34.939
so the angle starts out at 0.

00:47:34.939 --> 00:47:36.480
If you go to a high
enough frequency,

00:47:36.480 --> 00:47:40.470
both angles go 2 pi over 2.

00:47:40.470 --> 00:47:42.390
So they both angle--
so the difference

00:47:42.390 --> 00:47:45.421
goes to 0 at high
frequencies, as well.

00:47:45.421 --> 00:47:46.920
There's a little
blip in the middle,

00:47:46.920 --> 00:47:51.210
because the angle of the
zero increases more rapidly

00:47:51.210 --> 00:47:53.560
than the angle at the pole.

00:47:53.560 --> 00:47:57.780
0's in the top, so there's a
little blip for positive phase.

00:47:57.780 --> 00:48:01.680
Same sort of thing works if I
think about the mass, spring,

00:48:01.680 --> 00:48:02.400
dashpot system.

00:48:05.490 --> 00:48:09.510
Now if I write the-- so if I
just write the differential

00:48:09.510 --> 00:48:11.340
equation, figure out
the system function,

00:48:11.340 --> 00:48:15.720
I get a simple form that
looks like so, second order.

00:48:15.720 --> 00:48:19.320
If I imagine very
low damping, you

00:48:19.320 --> 00:48:22.810
can see that the poles are
going to have the form s

00:48:22.810 --> 00:48:26.810
squared m plus k must be 0.

00:48:26.810 --> 00:48:30.240
So they are complex.

00:48:30.240 --> 00:48:31.810
OK?

00:48:31.810 --> 00:48:36.220
So if you factor this, if
you set this equal to 0,

00:48:36.220 --> 00:48:39.160
you're going to get that
squared m plus k must be zero

00:48:39.160 --> 00:48:41.590
if b were small.

00:48:41.590 --> 00:48:44.740
So the poles are
going to be complex.

00:48:44.740 --> 00:48:46.300
So for example,
if the poles were,

00:48:46.300 --> 00:48:51.610
as indicated here, about
minus 1 plus or minus j 3,

00:48:51.610 --> 00:48:53.860
all you do is the same
thing we did before,

00:48:53.860 --> 00:48:55.350
consider the length
of the vectors,

00:48:55.350 --> 00:48:57.160
consider the angle
of the vectors.

00:48:57.160 --> 00:48:59.320
Here you get sum
product, and you

00:48:59.320 --> 00:49:01.570
get angles that are
complimentary, so

00:49:01.570 --> 00:49:04.330
plus and minus.

00:49:04.330 --> 00:49:07.630
So the angle starts out at 0.

00:49:07.630 --> 00:49:11.110
As you increase the
frequency, one of the pole--

00:49:11.110 --> 00:49:13.990
one of the arrows
gets longer and longer

00:49:13.990 --> 00:49:18.610
by about a factor of 2, and
the other gets shorter--

00:49:18.610 --> 00:49:22.540
gets shorter by a lot
more than a factor of 2.

00:49:22.540 --> 00:49:28.680
So that means that the product
of the lankes becomes small,

00:49:28.680 --> 00:49:33.070
but they're in the bottom, so
the eigenvalue becomes large.

00:49:33.070 --> 00:49:36.150
So that's what's going on here.

00:49:36.150 --> 00:49:38.730
So that's the idea.

00:49:38.730 --> 00:49:40.960
I've written two check
yourself questions.

00:49:40.960 --> 00:49:45.660
Those are intended to just be
practice with complex numbers,

00:49:45.660 --> 00:49:48.210
because you need to know
how to do complex numbers.

00:49:48.210 --> 00:49:54.480
But the point-- so
the point of today

00:49:54.480 --> 00:49:56.970
is just that there's a
very natural way-- that's

00:49:56.970 --> 00:49:59.370
completely complementary to
thinking about convolution

00:49:59.370 --> 00:50:00.570
in time.

00:50:00.570 --> 00:50:03.450
There's a different natural way
to think about some systems,

00:50:03.450 --> 00:50:05.430
in terms of the
frequency response.

00:50:05.430 --> 00:50:08.850
How does the system respond
to an eternal sine wave?

00:50:08.850 --> 00:50:11.130
It's a very easy
thing to compute.

00:50:11.130 --> 00:50:12.960
It follows very
naturally from the things

00:50:12.960 --> 00:50:14.730
that we thought about
with convolution,

00:50:14.730 --> 00:50:17.160
and the results quite amazing.

00:50:17.160 --> 00:50:19.680
The result is that the
magnitude of the angle

00:50:19.680 --> 00:50:23.850
can be computed from the
Laplace transform of the impulse

00:50:23.850 --> 00:50:27.130
response, which just happens
to be the system function.

00:50:27.130 --> 00:50:29.010
So the point-- so
hopefully, what you see

00:50:29.010 --> 00:50:30.870
is that we have lots
of representations,

00:50:30.870 --> 00:50:34.724
and now we're seeing even
more connections between them.

00:50:34.724 --> 00:50:35.580
OK.

00:50:35.580 --> 00:50:37.400
Have a good day.

